{"id":891,"date":"2014-04-17T18:00:00","date_gmt":"2014-04-17T18:00:00","guid":{"rendered":""},"modified":"2015-03-23T22:52:35","modified_gmt":"2015-03-23T22:52:35","slug":"kubuntu-14-04-lts","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/news\/kubuntu-14-04-lts\/","title":{"rendered":"Kubuntu 14.04 LTS"},"content":{"rendered":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http:\/\/kubwp.kubuntu.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/kubuntu-14.04-wee.jpg\" rel=\"lightbox[891]\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2042\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/kubuntu-14.04-wee.jpg\" alt=\"kubuntu-14.04-wee\" width=\"660\" height=\"207\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/kubuntu-14.04-wee.jpg 660w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/kubuntu-14.04-wee-300x94.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 660px) 100vw, 660px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Welcome to Kubuntu 14.04 LTS, a brand new Long Term Supported version with the latest KDE software to enjoy.<\/p>\n<p>Long Term Support means bugfixes and security updates will be added for the next 5 years, so you can be safe to use it until 2019. New releases of important KDE Software will also be available from the Kubuntu Updates and Kubuntu Backports PPAs.<\/p>\n<div>\n<table style=\"background: #E1F0FA; margin: 0 0 1em 1em;\">\n<tbody style=\"border-top: 0;\">\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 33%;\"><strong>Upgrading from 12.04 LTS<\/strong><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 33%;\"><strong>Upgrading from 13.10<\/strong><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 33%;\"><strong>Download a Disk Image<\/strong><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>To upgrade Kubuntu 12.04 LTS to Kubuntu 14.04 LTS, click on the notification which will appear in your panel.<br \/>\nSee <a href=\"https:\/\/help.ubuntu.com\/community\/TrustyUpgrades\/Kubuntu\/12.04LTS\">12.04 to 14.04 Upgrade Instructions<\/a> for a complete walkthrough.<\/td>\n<td>To upgrade from Kubuntu 13.10 to Kubuntu 14.04 LTS, click on the notification which will appear in your panel.<br \/>\nSee <a href=\"https:\/\/help.ubuntu.com\/community\/TrustyUpgrades\/Kubuntu\">13.10 to 14.04 Upgrade Instructions<\/a> for a complete walkthrough.<\/td>\n<td>Download a <a href=\"http:\/\/www.kubuntu.org\/getkubuntu\">bootable image<\/a> and put it onto a DVD or USB. <a href=\"https:\/\/help.ubuntu.com\/community\/BurningIsoHowto\">Burning ISO Guide<\/a>.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<\/div>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h1>Software Highlights of Kubuntu 14.04 LTS<\/h1>\n<h2>KDE Applications and Platform 4.13<\/h2>\n<table>\n<tbody style=\"border-top: 0;\">\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"http:\/\/kubwp.kubuntu.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/gwenview-promo.png\" rel=\"lightbox[891]\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-2012 size-full\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/gwenview-promo.png\" alt=\"gwenview-promo\" width=\"360\" height=\"319\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/gwenview-promo.png 360w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/gwenview-promo-300x266.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 360px) 100vw, 360px\" \/><\/a><\/td>\n<td>Fresh out today, the <a href=\"http:\/\/kde.org\/announcements\/4.13\/\">KDE Applications and Platform 4.13<\/a> release introduces a greatly improved semantic search as well as stabilization and improvements in key applications like Okular.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h2>Mozilla Firefox<\/h2>\n<table>\n<tbody style=\"border-top: 0;\">\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"http:\/\/kubwp.kubuntu.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/firefox-350px.png\" rel=\"lightbox[891]\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-2013 size-full\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/firefox-350px.png\" alt=\"firefox-350px\" width=\"350\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/firefox-350px.png 350w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/firefox-350px-300x171.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px\" \/><\/a><\/td>\n<td>Kubuntu 14.04 introduces award winning Mozilla Firefox as default web browser.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h2>Muon Discover 2.2<\/h2>\n<table>\n<tbody style=\"border-top: 0;\">\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"http:\/\/kubwp.kubuntu.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/muon-discover-350px.png\" rel=\"lightbox[891]\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-2014 size-full\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/muon-discover-350px.png\" alt=\"muon-discover-350px\" width=\"350\" height=\"257\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/muon-discover-350px.png 350w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/muon-discover-350px-300x220.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px\" \/><\/a><\/td>\n<td>Muon Suite 2.2 brings additional improvements to our Software Center applications, resolving various problems and offering an altogether more refined experience.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h2>All New Driver Manager<\/h2>\n<table>\n<tbody style=\"border-top: 0;\">\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"http:\/\/kubwp.kubuntu.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/driver-manager-350px.png\" rel=\"lightbox[891]\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-2015 size-full\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/driver-manager-350px.png\" alt=\"driver-manager-350px\" width=\"350\" height=\"240\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/driver-manager-350px.png 350w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/driver-manager-350px-300x206.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px\" \/><\/a><\/td>\n<td>The previous Additional Drivers application is being replaced by the all new Driver Manager. The manager allows you to install and select the driver you want to use for software that has more than one supported driver, including proprietary drivers.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h2>Gwenview Plugin Installation<\/h2>\n<table>\n<tbody style=\"border-top: 0;\">\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"http:\/\/kubwp.kubuntu.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/gwenview-plugins-350px.png\" rel=\"lightbox[891]\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-2016 size-full\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/gwenview-plugins-350px.png\" alt=\"gwenview-plugins-350px\" width=\"350\" height=\"260\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/gwenview-plugins-350px.png 350w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/gwenview-plugins-350px-300x223.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px\" \/><\/a><\/td>\n<td>Plugins in Gwenview can now be installed on-demand from inside the application.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h2>New Touchpad Configuration<\/h2>\n<table>\n<tbody style=\"border-top: 0;\">\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"http:\/\/kubwp.kubuntu.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/touchpad-350px.png\" rel=\"lightbox[891]\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-2017 size-full\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/touchpad-350px.png\" alt=\"touchpad-350px\" width=\"350\" height=\"213\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/touchpad-350px.png 350w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/touchpad-350px-300x183.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px\" \/><\/a><\/td>\n<td>Our new touchpad configuration tools includes many configuration options to get your touchpad working just as you like.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h2>KDE Instant Messaging 0.8<\/h2>\n<table>\n<tbody style=\"border-top: 0;\">\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"http:\/\/kubwp.kubuntu.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/ktp-350px.png\" rel=\"lightbox[891]\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-2018 size-full\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/ktp-350px.png\" alt=\"ktp-350px\" width=\"350\" height=\"301\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/ktp-350px.png 350w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/ktp-350px-300x258.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px\" \/><\/a><\/td>\n<td>KDE Telepathy now has a meta contact support for grouping the same contact across different IM networks. The new release also includes more stability and polish than ever before.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h2>Improved Localization Configuration<\/h2>\n<table>\n<tbody style=\"border-top: 0;\">\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"http:\/\/kubwp.kubuntu.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/kcm-locale-350px.png\" rel=\"lightbox[891]\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-2019 size-full\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/kcm-locale-350px.png\" alt=\"kcm-locale-350px\" width=\"350\" height=\"230\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/kcm-locale-350px.png 350w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/kcm-locale-350px-300x197.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px\" \/><\/a><\/td>\n<td>Language configuration has seen numerous changes, improving reliability and localization coverage beyond KDE technology.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h2>Plasma Network Manager 0.9.3.3<\/h2>\n<table>\n<tbody style=\"border-top: 0;\">\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"http:\/\/kubwp.kubuntu.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/plasma-nm-350px.png\" rel=\"lightbox[891]\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-2020 size-full\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/plasma-nm-350px.png\" alt=\"plasma-nm-350px\" width=\"350\" height=\"235\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/plasma-nm-350px.png 350w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/plasma-nm-350px-300x201.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px\" \/><\/a><\/td>\n<td>The new Plasma Network Manager features a redesigned user interface, giving you more control while retaining a simple design.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h2>KDE Software Development Kit<\/h2>\n<table>\n<tbody style=\"border-top: 0;\">\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"http:\/\/kubwp.kubuntu.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/kde-sdk-350px.png\" rel=\"lightbox[891]\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-2021 size-full\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/kde-sdk-350px.png\" alt=\"kde-sdk-350px\" width=\"350\" height=\"207\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/kde-sdk-350px.png 350w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/kde-sdk-350px-300x177.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px\" \/><\/a><\/td>\n<td>The newly available KDE software development kit equips new installations with everything necessary to write beautiful code using KDE and Qt technology, allowing everyone to quickly get started with writing code on Kubuntu 14.04.<br \/>\nInstall <em>kde-developer-sdk<\/em> to get started.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h2>USB Creator Improvements<\/h2>\n<table>\n<tbody style=\"border-top: 0;\">\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"http:\/\/kubwp.kubuntu.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/usb-creator-kde-350px.png\" rel=\"lightbox[891]\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-2022 size-full\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/usb-creator-kde-350px.png\" alt=\"usb-creator-kde-350px\" width=\"350\" height=\"378\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/usb-creator-kde-350px.png 350w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/usb-creator-kde-350px-278x300.png 278w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px\" \/><\/a><\/td>\n<td>USB Creator has seen some nice bugfixes. Disks are selected when you expect them to, widgets can&#8217;t be shrunk to be too small, list sizing is done smartly.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h2>KDE Connect 0.5<\/h2>\n<table>\n<tbody style=\"border-top: 0;\">\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"http:\/\/kubwp.kubuntu.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/kdeconnect-350px.png\" rel=\"lightbox[891]\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-2023 size-full\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/kdeconnect-350px.png\" alt=\"kdeconnect-350px\" width=\"350\" height=\"164\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/kdeconnect-350px.png 350w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/kdeconnect-350px-300x141.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px\" \/><\/a><\/td>\n<td>Install KDE Connect on your desktop and your Android mobile phone to integrate the two. Text messages will appear on your screen, files can be shared, your music can be controlled from your phone and your music will be turned off when you receive a phone call.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h2>Automatic Crash Reporting<\/h2>\n<table>\n<tbody style=\"border-top: 0;\">\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"http:\/\/kubwp.kubuntu.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/drkonqi-whoopsie-350px.png\" rel=\"lightbox[891]\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-2024 size-full\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/drkonqi-whoopsie-350px.png\" alt=\"drkonqi-whoopsie-350px\" width=\"350\" height=\"204\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/drkonqi-whoopsie-350px.png 350w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/drkonqi-whoopsie-350px-300x175.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px\" \/><\/a><\/td>\n<td>No software is perfect; Kubuntu 14.04 makes it easier than ever before to inform developers when something has gone terribly wrong, using the all new automatic crash reporting.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h2>Quassel 0.10<\/h2>\n<table>\n<tbody style=\"border-top: 0;\">\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"http:\/\/kubwp.kubuntu.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/quassel-350px.png\" rel=\"lightbox[891]\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-2025 size-full\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/quassel-350px.png\" alt=\"quassel-350px\" width=\"350\" height=\"209\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/quassel-350px.png 350w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/quassel-350px-300x179.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px\" \/><\/a><\/td>\n<td>The IRC client Quassel 0.10 reduces network traffic while improving overall reliability.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h2>New System Notifications<\/h2>\n<table>\n<tbody style=\"border-top: 0;\">\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"http:\/\/kubwp.kubuntu.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/knh-350px.png\" rel=\"lightbox[891]\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-2026 size-full\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/knh-350px.png\" alt=\"knh-350px\" width=\"350\" height=\"210\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/knh-350px.png 350w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/knh-350px-300x180.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px\" \/><\/a><\/td>\n<td>Kubuntu&#8217;s built-in recommendation software now notifies you when better drivers for your hardware can be installed and when additional software can be installed to improve the language support.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h1>Known Problems<\/h1>\n<ul>\n<li>The software updater can close unexpectedly in very specific complicated update scenarios (Bug <a href=\"https:\/\/bugs.launchpad.net\/ubuntu\/+source\/muon\/+bug\/1295437\">#1295437<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/bugs.launchpad.net\/ubuntu\/+source\/muon\/+bug\/1295440\">#1295440<\/a>)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Additional problems being tracked can be found at <a href=\"https:\/\/tinyurl.com\/ovfcj78\">Kubuntu 14.04 milestoned bugs<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>Problems in the installer, graphics and kernel are listed on the <a href=\"https:\/\/wiki.kubuntu.org\/TrustyTahr\/ReleaseNotes#Known_issues\">common release notes.<\/a><\/p>\n<h1>Commercial Support<\/h1>\n<table>\n<tbody style=\"border-top: 0;\">\n<tr>\n<td>Our <a href=\"http:\/\/kubuntu.emerge-open.com\/buy\">commercial support offering<\/a> is now open, available for those who need the reassurance of help on the end of a phone line.<\/td>\n<td><a href=\"http:\/\/kubuntu.emerge-open.com\/buy\"><br \/>\n<img src=\"https:\/\/wiki.ubuntu.com\/TrustyTahr\/Final\/Kubuntu?action=AttachFile&amp;do=get&amp;target=emerge-350px.jpg\" alt=\"\" \/><br \/>\n<\/a><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h1>Feedback<\/h1>\n<p>Tell us what you think about <a href=\"https:\/\/plus.google.com\/b\/107577785796696065138\/107577785796696065138\/posts\/hbnWSoY4Gcz\">Kubuntu 14.04 LTS on Google+<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p><!-- Place this tag where you want the widget to render. --><\/p>\n<div class=\"g-page\" data-width=\"350\" data-href=\"https:\/\/plus.google.com\/107577785796696065138\" data-rel=\"publisher\"><\/div>\n<p><!-- Place this tag after the last widget tag. --><br \/>\n<script type=\"text\/javascript\">\/\/ <![CDATA[\n(function() {     var po = document.createElement('script'); po.type = 'text\/javascript'; po.async = true;     po.src = 'https:\/\/apis.google.com\/js\/platform.js';     var s = document.getElementsByTagName('script')[0]; s.parentNode.insertBefore(po, s);   })();\n\/\/ ]]><\/script><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Welcome to Kubuntu 14.04 LTS, a brand new Long Term Supported version with the latest KDE software to enjoy. Long Term Support means bugfixes and security updates will be added for the next 5 years, so you can be safe to use it until 2019. New releases of important KDE&#8230;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":3,"featured_media":2042,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[129],"tags":[138,177,183],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/891"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=891"}],"version-history":[{"count":6,"href":"https:\/